## Specification

A specification is represented as a Groovy class that extends from `spock.lang.Specification`.

@1579181219157
Order of elements in specification
class MyFirstSpecification extends Specification {
  // {{c1::fields}}
  // {{c2::fixture methods}}
  // {{c3::feature methods}}
  // {{c4::helper methods}}
}

@1579181219209
Class {{c1::Specification}} contains a number of useful methods for writing specifications. Furthermore it instructs JUnit to run specification with {{c2::Sputnik}}, Spockâ€™s {{c3::JUnit runner}}. Thanks to {{c2::Sputnik}}, Spock specifications can be run by most modern Java IDEs and build tools.

